// MANDATORY BROWSER TESTING FOR WEB FEATURES AND FIXES
//
// When implementing or fixing any web frontend features, UI components, or web-related functionality,
// you MUST use the browser tools available in Cursor to test the changes before marking the task as complete.
//
// REQUIREMENTS:
//
// 1. BROWSER TESTING IS MANDATORY
//    - All web features, UI changes, frontend fixes, and Streamlit app modifications MUST be tested
//      using browser tools before considering the task complete
//    - Never mark a task as "done" or "tested" without actual browser verification
//    - Code-only testing (unit tests, manual code review) is NOT sufficient for web features
//
// 2. APPLICATION URL
//    - Default test URL: http://localhost:8502 (Streamlit app runs on port 8502)
//    - Ensure the application is running before testing (use: uv run streamlit run src/app.py --server.port 8502)
//    - Navigate to the URL using browser_navigate tool
//
// 3. TESTING WORKFLOW
//    - Navigate to the application URL
//    - Use browser_snapshot to capture the current state
//    - Interact with the feature/fix using browser tools (click, type, select, etc.)
//    - Verify the expected behavior actually works in the browser
//    - Check for visual issues, broken UI elements, JavaScript errors, or unexpected behavior
//    - Use browser_console_messages to check for errors
//
// 4. ITERATION REQUIREMENT
//    - If browser testing reveals issues, you MUST fix them and re-test
//    - Continue iterating on fixes until the feature works correctly in the browser
//    - Do not consider the task complete until browser testing confirms it works
//
// 5. SCOPE
//    - Applies to: Streamlit UI changes, frontend components, form interactions, map visualizations,
//      data display, user interactions, styling changes, responsive design, and any web-facing feature
//    - Even small UI tweaks must be verified in the browser
//
// 6. DOCUMENTATION
//    - Document any limitations or known issues discovered during browser testing
//    - Note if certain browsers or conditions affect functionality
//
// EXAMPLE WORKFLOW:
// 1. Make code changes
// 2. Start/restart the Streamlit app if needed
// 3. Use browser_navigate to go to http://localhost:8502
// 4. Use browser_snapshot to see the current state
// 5. Interact with the feature (click buttons, fill forms, etc.)
// 6. Verify expected behavior
// 7. Check console for errors
// 8. If issues found, fix and repeat from step 3
// 9. Only mark as complete when browser testing confirms it works
//
// REMEMBER: Browser tools exist for this exact purpose - to catch issues that only appear
// when viewing the application in an actual browser. Use them!
